<p>I have a numpy array:</p>  <pre><code>array([[ 0.68597575,  0.05544651, -1.        ],        [ 0.33494648,  0.46368367,  1.        ],        [ 0.42486765,  0.89427025,  1.        ],        [ 0.62408611,  0.64633939,  1.        ],        [ 0.37087957,  0.53077302, -1.        ],        [ 0.21664159,  0.10786084, -1.        ],        [ 0.13003626,  0.18425347, -1.        ]]) </code></pre>  <p>I want the rows having last values <code>-1</code> to be multiplied by -1 and also replaced in the actual matrix.</p>  <p>I tried this:</p>  <pre><code>def transform(data):     for row in data:         if row[-1] == -1:             row = row * -1 </code></pre>  <p>but I know there would be something simpler than this.</p>